title: Close-up of Emma limping soon after her injury
tags: International Tiger Project|ITP|Emma the tiger|Camera trap|Wire snare|Snare trap|Tiger caught in snare trap|Tiger survival|Saving tigers|Save the tiger|Tiger video|Big cats|Wild tiger|Sumatran tiger|Sumatran rainforest|Wildlife Protection Units|Wildlife protection|Wildlife rangers
description: This video is both a beautiful portrait of Emma the tiger and a heartbreaking demonstration of her injury. We believe she became caught in a snare trap, which had been set in the forest, possibly to catch species like wild boar. Although she's clearly been injured by the trap, Emma is one of the 'lucky' ones, because she managed to escape. Most tigers caught in traps don't survive.
